        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 9:37AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Light snow will continue to move southward through the plains and
into Central Montana through this afternoon. The snow will reduce
visibility to less than a mile at times and road surfaces may
become slippery from slushy snow accumulation. Road surfaces
should begin to become wet as daytime heating increases later this
morning and afternoon.

Snowfall amounts will mostly range from trace amounts up to a
couple of inches. Take care and allow extra time to reach your
destination.
</description>
